        <detaileddescription>
<para>Updates the GamepadState objects with the current values of the underlying hardware. If querying the underlying hardware fails, this method will update the GamepadState values to a valid initial state (no movement or interaction). Implementations should use `isConnected()` to check whether the current values of a `GamepadState` object can be trusted.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>gamepadMask</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A bitmask representing all GamepadState objects to update, e.g. Gamepad::ONE | Gamepad::TWO...    </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
